    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="624"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 625.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copies of two letters<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d624fn1">Not printed.</note> from the chairman of the Juragua Iron
                    Company, Limited, stating that that company has been threatened by the Cuban
                    insurgents with destruction of the works unless they should have paid by the
                    30th ultimo an indemnity fund of $1,000,000 and export dues amounting to $3,000
                    per month on ore shipped.</p>
                <p>You will bring this matter to the attention of the Spanish Government, and
                    request that it may give immediate and complete protection to the company’s
                    property against any attempt on the part of the insurgents to carry out the
                    above-mentioned threat.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
